public interface GraphLoader extends com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.Repeater
A graph loader takes data from some data source and loads it into a GraphStore, applying a set of constraints that potentially limits which graph elements are loaded and which are not. Graph loaders are only responsible for reading data and adding it to the provided GraphStore. Details about how the Graph and GraphStore manage the loaded details are private to those objects.

Graph loaders are implementation details for loading Graph objects from various data sources. If you need to load a GraphArchive, use GraphArchive.load(Listener). If you need to load some other kind of graph resource, use the SmartGraphLoader, which will load graphs from any supported format: 

     private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.newLogger();
       [...]
     var resource = new File(...);
     var graph = new SmartGraphLoader(resource).load(LOGGER);

  • Method Details

    • onCommit

      default void onCommit(GraphStore store)
      Called when loading is complete to allow finalization of the loaded data. For example, this is where OSM grade separations are added based on the final OSM graph.
      Parameters:
      store - The graph into which data has been loaded

    • onLoad

      Metadata onLoad(GraphStore store, GraphConstraints constraints)
      Called to load edge and vertex data into the given graph from some storage medium.
      Parameters:
      store - The graph store to load data into
      constraints - The constraints restricting what graph elements should be added to the graph
      Returns:
      Metadata describing the data that was loaded

    • resource

      com.telenav.kivakit.resource.Resource resource()
      Returns:
      The resource from which loaded data originates. In the case of a database or some similar source that is not a Resource, the value returned may be null.

    • validation

      default com.telenav.kivakit.validation.ValidationType validation()
      Returns:
      The kind of validation that should be performed on the data loaded by this graph loader. Many graph loaders validate all data with ValidationType.VALIDATE_ALL but some don't load complete data. An example of an incomplete graph loader is RawPbfGraphLoader, which does not load vertexes or relations. Another is WaySectioningGraphLoader, is incomplete because it does not load relations. These graph loaders may specify another kind of validation.
